<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-0B63D7A2-D9BF-4912-ADFF-D7D72783FF3A" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-0B63D7A2-D9BF-4912-ADFF-D7D72783FF3A" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Clean the ink unit</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-EFDBB09F-FB2C-42D5-8A95-DAFF0F2A18D8"><p class="- topic/p "> It is advised to clean the ink unit regularly to keep the printer in the best condition. You can clean the ink unit when you replace a bottle or during periodic maintenance. When you see ink pollution, immediately clean the affected area. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Video: <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="Video: 8 - Clean the ink unit"><xref class="- topic/xref " format="html" href="https://sus.cpp.canon/9XDYPQ4K" scope="external"><?ditaot usertext?> 
<image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-1B93C780-C233-4810-947C-7EC17F913975-low.png"/> Clean the ink unit</xref></ph>. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">User task</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-57608119-5922-41A2-A153-390B88D005E7" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><p class="- topic/p ">Use <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> prescribed: 
</p><ul id="UL_88FE82F1C6B343028F9B61DB8C430ED7" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_F4B9AC154F1445FBAA8F889824E6FD43" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph ">Microflex</ph> gloves for handling ink 
</p></li><li id="LI_6FA5A3A7E0FE4587B6D4539C231C8B45" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Lint free cloths 
</p></li><li id="LI_CB737E3FC4D04C7AA5607B614DF66F03" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Cleaning liquid (IPA) 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-153CC759-3960-41C2-B43D-821B59856AAF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">For information on the prescribed maintenance material. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-E1574C6E-8EA7-467B-8618-101E26AF4C2D" class="- topic/note " type="caution"><p class="- topic/p "> Wear gloves when contact with ink or maintenance materials is possible. Gloves should always overlap sleeves. Wear safety glasses with side shields when handling ink or maintenance materials. Follow the ink related Safety Data Sheets (SDS) guidelines carefully in order to ensure maximum safety. 
</p></note><note id="GUID-45943B5B-03BA-4B5B-A42A-D6D1F808D388" class="- topic/note " type="important"><p class="- topic/p "> Use the prescribed cleaning liquid. Do not use any other cleaners. 
</p></note></prereq><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-9848D934-FF3E-4AC9-BA07-69028FA44036" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><steps id="GUID-5AEBECEA-F3DC-4CB7-9E21-23D31200507E" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="d4998e59" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Go to the side of the printer where the ink bottles are located. 
</cmd></step><step id="d4998e62" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Put on the <ph varid="productname" class="- topic/ph ">Colorado M-Series</ph> approved gloves. 
</cmd></step><step id="d4998e68" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Move down the green handle which is located left of the bottle you want to replace. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not hold the bottle while you move the handle. 
</p></info><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="d4998e75" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-8F18A24E-0A06-4A29-9294-00BCAD8FFDE6-low.png" id="d4998e76" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-8F18A24E-0A06-4A29-9294-00BCAD8FFDE6-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d4998e77" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take the empty bottle out of the slot. 
</cmd></step><step id="d4998e80" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Dispose the bottle as chemical waste according to local regulations. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">If preferred and possible, you can repeat the steps to take out all bottles. 
</p></info></step><step id="d4998e86" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take a lint free cloth and clean the indicated areas surrounding the slots until all residue ink is gone. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">If necessary, dampen a swab with the cleaning liquid to remove any remaining ink. 
</p><fig id="d4998e92" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-50121C7D-BB3D-40EF-B17F-685B0C792FBE-low.png" id="d4998e93" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-50121C7D-BB3D-40EF-B17F-685B0C792FBE-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="d4998e94" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">When all residue ink is removed, dispose the gloves and cloths as chemical waste according to local regulations. 
</cmd></step></steps><result id="RESULT_13374D42133C4B26B4705DC663D34D4E" class="- topic/section task/result "><p class="- topic/p ">If preferred and possible, you can place new bottles and refill ink. If the machine is not equipped with white ink, the order of the bottles from left to right is YCMK. If the machine is equipped with white ink, the order of the bottles from left to right is YCMKW. 
</p></result></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7C646994-2512-42B4-9724-5A191152EE30.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>User task</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>